27. find / -type f -name *.conf -user root -size +20k -newermt 2020-03-03 -exec ls -al {} \; 2>/dev/null       
here -type f defines file search                
here -name *.conf defines config file to search            
here -user root defines all files whose owner is root          
here -size +20k defines that size of file should be larger than   20kb            
here -newermt 2020-03-03 defines that only file show wbose date is newer than this date              
here -exec ls -al {} \; defines Executes ls -la on each file or directory found by find, displaying detailed information for every result.  -exec do For every file found, run this command. {} is for placeholder (eg= ./notes.txt) \; use to end exec command                 
here 2>/dev/null defines Redirects error messages (stderr) to /dev/null, hiding them from the terminal.          
